>
[snip]
>
>      (3) the number of Voting Tokens possessed by each Entity other
>          than the Bank is adjusted to be one tenth of its previous
>          value, and to each such decrease caused by this adjustment
>          there corresponds an equivalent increase in the number of
>          Voting Tokens held by the Bank.

The business of making exceptions is a dangerous one, but I feel that
Kolja and possibly Elde should probably be excepted, or at least
treated differently, when the above adjustment is made, since they
were not registered during the period of high VT supply, and hence
did not benefit from it. My idea is to add these paragraphs to the
Proposal:

      (4) if the number of Voting Tokens possessed by Elde after 
          the adjustment performed above in (3) is less than 5, 
          then the number of Voting Tokens possessed by Elde is 
          adjusted to be 5, and to the increase caused by this
          adjustment there corresponds an equivalent decrease in
          the number of Voting Tokens held by the Bank.

      (5) if the number of Voting Tokens possessed by Kolja A. after 
          the adjustment performed above in (3) is less than 5, 
          then the number of Voting Tokens possessed by Kolja A. is 
          adjusted to be 5, and to the increase caused by this
          adjustment there corresponds an equivalent decrease in
          the number of Voting Tokens held by the Bank.

Any objections?

Note that since Elde is Maybe Absent, it's quite possible he'll be
deregistered before this takes effect, obviating the need for (4).

